== Availability ==
The Hyperion cannot be bought and must be [[Bigship Boarding|boarded]]. It can be found patrolling some Paranid sectors, sometimes unescorted.

When choosing the starting game scenario "Poisoned Paranid" you get an "overtuned" Hyperion upon paying the ransom for it. This Hyperion is special in that it can (by chance) reach very high speed levels, reportedly up to 250.2 m/s. [{{linky}}forum.egosoft.com/viewtopic.php?t=289489 See details.]

== Suggested Roles==
The Hyperion is an excellent player ship due to its versatility and ability to beat any other ship in a fight, with sufficient skill from the pilot.

The ship's large cargo hold, docking bay, speed and maneuverability effectively make it an exceptionally powerful TM class ship. Capable of launching a small (2) wing of fighters, deploy large objects like lasertowers or fighter drone swarms, or act as a missile platform; the Hyperion is one of the most versatile ships in space.
*As a Warship, it can mount 8 CIG or ISR as main guns, plus 4 EBC and 6 PAC in its turrets. It can hold 400 Wraith (vs. capital ships), 400 Typhoon (vs. fighters), 100 wasp (vs. fleeing fighters), 200 Mosquito (vs. incoming missiles) and still have energy for 100 sector jump range.
*As a fast trader, it is extremely resilient, powerful and fast. Its cargo hold multiplied by its speed is better than even the TS class [[Mistral]]. Only the [[Springblossom]] might be a better at this role, as it is weaker, but much faster.
*As a complex building ship, it is the second fastest ship able to mount a Tractor Beam (the Split [[Dragon]] is 3 m/s faster). This shortens the time traveling when not towing factories (as it is capped at 80 m/s).

